EMS Patient Care Report Narrative Section

text.paragraph: S Called for motor vehicle crash

O Restrained make patient found in driver's seat of 4-door sedan. Pt unresponsive. Law enforcement holding c-spine and placed nasal airway for snoring respirations. Bystanders state vehicle swerved off road and came to stop. Exam showed Pt suffered a gun shot wound to L side at 5th intercostal space.
B Labored at 22 with decreased lung sounds
D Decreased level of consciousness with GCS = 9, AVPU = P

E HEENT: intact, no trauma noted. Neck: supple, no JVD; Trachea midline. Chest: GSW as noted; decreased LS to left side. ABD: soft nontender. Pelvis: intact. GI: intact. Ext: moves all extremities with pupose upon painful stimulation, no trauma noted.

PLAN C collar, nasal airway with O2 @ 15 LPM via NRB, LSB, monitor. Sinus tach, no ectopy, occlusive dressing. Reassess: O2 sats decreased, labored breathing. Treatment: needle chest decompression L side. Transport lights and siren. Enroute two IVs established. Diverted to XXX hospital. Breathing improved. Care and report to ED staff.
